so we had a swim meet last night and we won!! YAY! it came down to me in the last race... but this is how the night when for me...

I first swam the 200 free which i have never swam before and i did really good and stayed in front of the girl in the lane next to me. well the last 25 she sped up and caught up to me and she touched me out... she beat me by like .25 second... i finished with my arm bent and not extended but it was the first time i have swam that enent and according to val, i did good for that being my first time... so i could have beat her but oh well... Next.. then i did the 100 fly like i have been doing. i was behind the girl in the lane right next to me the hole time until the last 25 where i sped up and caught up to her (sound farmilular?) well i took an extra stroke insttead of just a kick but i came really close to her... she beat me by like .3 second.... BUT i dropped 4 seconds on it so i was still proud of myself. After that i was in the 200 free relay (4 swimmers swim a 50 each) so i was the anchor (last oout of the 4 to go) i kicked ass and went into the water behind lane 5 ( i was in lane 2) and i touched her out!!!! it was sweet. i got a personal best time in that also. so when i got out of the pool from doing that val came up to me and told me that she was going to switch me out of the C relay (klowest relay) to the A relay (highest) and i was all freaking out ,,, oh btw this is for the 400 relay that was still to come.... and so i was the anchor for that.. katie johnson who was in my relay got in my head and her, Chris carter and Tori Laduke all got me a huge lead going to in the last 1-- that i had to do. i ended up going like a 1:09 and thats like 15 second sbetter than my other times!!!!! it was awesome.. that was the race it came down to and i was so far ahead of all the all lanes and i won it adn it was awesome.. i coudln't have done it without the support of my relay mates.. and the fact that they got me such a huge lead from the get go. so we finally won a meet!!!! LOOK OUT EATON RAPIDS!!! so yea.... ok so now time for the stuff that is happening today...

We had morning practice this morning.... it was pretty easy. and at 3 we have swim practice... its like 3-6 which is like 45 mins longer than what we normally swim after school. after practice i am going to Jackson Northwest's homecominng game with matt... it should be fun and i will be meeting some of his friends... i'm excited. then tomorrow i am going to babysit from 8am- 2pm and then go to a church thing with matt... can't wait then he will be spending the night here at my house so that he can go to church with me on sunday morning.... this is going to eb a great weekend.. well i'll post how things go tomorrow or tonight which ever is better... c ya bitches...
